- 1.0.5 | Mar 16 2026:

  [Fix] All rm -f calls use 'command rm -f' to bypass potential user aliases
      on target systems; 17 instances across all delivery and cleanup paths
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: JSON-escape $channels and $file_id in
      completeUploadExternal request body; prevents malformed JSON from
      channel names containing special characters
  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message: replace awk -v with ENVIRON pattern for
      channel injection; prevents backslash interpretation in channel names
  [Fix] _alert_html_escape: use printf '%s' output (no trailing newline) to
      match _alert_json_escape, _alert_telegram_escape, _alert_slack_escape
  [New] _alert_deliver_email: validate non-empty recipient at function entry
  [New] _alert_slack_post_message: validate payload_file exists before
      processing; matches _alert_slack_upload validation pattern
  [New] Tests for telegram_document missing chat_id, Reply-To in text-sendmail
      fallback, empty email recipient validation, Slack channel JSON escaping,
      Slack payload_file guard, Slack channel backslash preservation (ENVIRON)
  [Change] README: add ALERT_EMAIL_REPLY_TO to environment variables table,
      add _alert_redact_url to API reference, update version badge and test
      counts
